President Obama has signed an emergency declaration for the state of New Hampshire due to the conditions caused by Hurricane Sandy. This declaration allows the Department of Homeland Security and FEMA to coordinate relief efforts and provide assistance to alleviate hardship and suffering. FEMA is authorized to mobilize resources and equipment to lessen the impact of the emergency. Emergency protective measures will be funded at 75 percent federal funding. Kevin L. Hannes has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area.